  "texts": [
    "These findings indicate that some universities have acknowledged the importance of tailored policies that recognize the diverse applications of ChatGPT in higher education.",
    "This is consistent with the studies of Chan and Lee [10] and Xiao et al. [56], which suggest an urgent need for upholding a flexible policy framework to accommodate the evolving nature of generative AI, enabling it to revolutionize teaching and learning.The restriction of access to ChatGPT may have temporarily slowed down the problem of academic dishonesty in Hong Kong.",
    "Compared with unrestricted regions like the UK, nearly 400 university students were investigated in July 2023 for using ChatGPT to plagiarize assignments [40].",
    "The use of ChatGPT is becoming increasingly prevalent in educational systems around the world, particularly in unrestricted regions.",
    "Therefore, it is essential to learn from other countries regarding university policies and practices developed to integrate ChatGPT in higher education settings."
